      "id": "u56_wrong_house",
      "title": "UNIT 56 — The Wrong House",
      "text": "How would you like to drive up to your house and find a pile of wood where your home once stood? It happened to Dorothy Irwin! When Irwin drove up on January 12, 1972, she saw a bulldozer knocking her house to pieces. “What are you doing?” she screamed. The operator said that he was told to demolish a vacant house on Raven Street. “Oh, no!” she said. “You have knocked down the wrong house!” A year earlier in 1971, her house had been slightly damaged by an earthquake. Dorothy Irwin planned to move back in, but the bulldozer got there first. Now she has a new house—and for free. The insurance company paid the bill.",
